PRIVACY POLICY 


Your privacy is very important to us. The following Privacy Policy sets forth our online privacy with respect to the collection of non-public personal information in connection with the operation of this Website. By accessing and/or using this Website, you signify your consent to the collection, storage, and disclosure of data as described in this Privacy Policy.  


We may modify this Privacy Policy at any time.  Changes in this Privacy Policy shall be deemed effective once posted on this Website.  Your continued use of this Website signifies acceptance by you of any changed terms to this Privacy Policy.  


Collection. We may collect information from you from a variety of different sources, including correspondence and discussions with you, information we receive from you on applications or other forms or documents you provide to us, and information about your transactions with us, our affiliates or others.  This information may include names, addresses, e-mail addresses, social security numbers, tax identification numbers and financial and other information we feel is necessary or useful in evaluating your ability to invest in our funds, in processing and managing your investment, or otherwise in furtherance of our business. In addition, to access password protected areas of the Website, you will be required to provide your user name and password, which permits us to identify you and associate you with the personal information you have provided to us in the past. We refer to all of this information collectively as your personally identifiable information.


We may also collect certain information automatically through the use of "cookies" and other technologies that we use in connection with the administration of this Website, including, without limitation, your browser type and operating system, your Internet Protocal (IP) address, sites you visited before or after visiting this Website, web pages you click from clicking on links within an e-mail message sent to you by us, and standard server log information.  We collect such information in order to enhance the content and functionality of this Website.  We will not collect any personal contact information from you (such as your name, e-mail, mailing address or phone number) unless you provide such information directly to us.  


Disclosure/Use. We may provide your nonpublic personal information to our affiliates and third party firms that perform services on our behalf and have a need for such information. Third party service providers that perform services on our behalf, such as a third party service provider that hosts this Website, may have access to certain of your information in connection with your visit to this Website. Companies that we hire to provide support services are not authorized to use your personal information for their own purposes and are obligated to maintain confidentiality of such information.  We do not provide your personally identifiable information to mailing list vendors or solicitors for any purpose.  By accessing and using this Website, you hereby authorize us to make available any information you provide to us, including personally identifiable information, to the third party that hosts this Website to the extent reasonably necessary to facilitate the use and operation of this Website. 


Cookies. As noted above, this Website uses "cookies" which automatically collect certain non-personal information and data. "Cookies" are small pieces of data sent to your computer browser from our web server and stored on your computer's hard drive. The data identifies you as a unique user and facilitates your ongoing access to and use of the site. Cookies also help us diagnose problems with our server.  We do not use cookies to retrieve personal information about you from your computer.  


You have the right to set your browser to accept or reject all cookies or to notify you when a cookie is set.  Please note that if you block cookies, you may not be able to view or access certain areas of this Website.  


Confidentiality and Security. When we provide personal information to a service provider, we expect these providers to safeguard your information, to use the information only for the intended purposes and to abide by applicable laws.  We restrict access to your nonpublic personal information to those employees with a valid business reason to have access to your personal information.  We do not otherwise provide information about you to outside firms, organizations or individuals except to certain third party service providers and except as permitted or required by law or requested or approved by you.  We maintain physical, electronic and procedural safeguards that comply with federal regulations to guard your nonpublic personal information. 






